The article discusses the progress made by the U.S. government in implementing reforms to improve hostage recovery efforts. President Obama had ordered comprehensive updates to U.S. hostage recovery policy and signed an Executive Order to organize efforts more effectively. The Hostage Recovery Fusion Cell was established to bring together law enforcement, intelligence, and military experts to develop recovery strategies. A Special Presidential Envoy for Hostage Affairs was also designated to coordinate diplomatic efforts. The interagency Hostage Response Group ensures that all elements are working together as a team. A status report, completed one year after the Executive Order was signed, concluded that the institutional and policy changes have had a positive impact on hostage recovery efforts. Departments and agencies have begun implementing recommendations for further improvements. The U.S. government remains committed to the safe recovery of its citizens and providing support to their families.